, transverse section of the ovule (SAR40C2T09); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[854,864,1657,1674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="59">J</emphasis>
, rachis of possible lyginopterid affinities showing five mesarch xylem bundles (arrows). Scale bars: A, B, G-J, 
<quantity box="[687,737,1680,1697]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; C-F, 
<quantity box="[784,850,1680,1697]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[677,1210,216,338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="60">
Pennsylvanian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1845" box="[848,991,217,242]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Pteridospermopsida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Heterangium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridospermopsida (awaiting allocation)" pageId="17" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[848,991,217,242]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="60">Heterangium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="PIGG K. B. &amp; TAYLOR T. N. &amp; STOCKEY R. A." pageId="17" pageNumber="60" pagination="1184 - 1204" refId="ref13633" refString="PIGG K. B., TAYLOR T. N. &amp; STOCKEY R. A. 1987. - Paleozoic seed ferns: Heterangium kentuckiensis sp. nov., from the Upper Carboniferous of North America. Amer. J. Bot. 74: 1184 - 1204." type="journal article" year="1987">
Pigg 
